HEADWORD: Diphtheria
<hw>Diph*the"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ leather (hence taken in the sense of <ets>membrane</ets>): cf. <?/
to make soft, L. <ets>depsere</ets> to knead.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A very dangerous contagious disease in which the air passages, and
especially the throat, become coated with a false membrane, produced by
the solidification of an inflammatory exudation. Cf.
<er>Group</er>.</def></p>

